main event: A witness reported seeing a slow-moving gray object through a window.
interesting points: The object was described as a 'star object' moving very slowly.
The witness was William McNeil, from a location in New Hampshire.
The object was observed for approximately 1 minute.
The Air Force investigation concluded the object was a Martin aircraft at 25,000 feet.
The document mentions a list of 'OE Reports' with dates, suggesting there may have been additional related sightings.
